          "text": "# AGENTS.md instructions for /Users/jserv/lkmpg\n\n<INSTRUCTIONS>\n# AGENTS.md\n\nThis file provides guidance to coding agents working in this repository.\n\n## Project\n\nLaTeX book (`lkmpg.tex`) with working Linux kernel module examples for 5.x/6.x kernels.\n\n## Build\n\n```bash\nmake                    # PDF via latexmk (needs texlive + pygments)\nmake html               # HTML via make4ht\nmake indent             # clang-format all examples/*.[ch]\n```\n\nKernel modules under `examples/` are Linux-only. Do not build them on macOS. Use `lima` to get a Linux VM, then build and test inside it:\n\n```bash\nlima make -C examples        # Build .ko modules\nlima .ci/build-n-run.sh      # Build + insmod/rmmod\n```\n\n## CI\n\nScripts in `.ci/`:\n\n- `check-format.sh`: clang-format compliance\n- `check-newline.sh`: trailing newline on all files in `examples/`\n- `static-analysis.sh`: `cppcheck`, `sparse`, `gcc -fanalyzer`, `smatch`\n- `build-n-run.sh`: build + `insmod`/`rmmod` twice per module, skipping `.ci/non-working`\n\n## Code Style\n\nC files follow `examples/.clang-format`:\n\n- 4-space indent\n- 80-column limit\n- Linux brace style\n- right-aligned pointers\n\nRun `make indent` before committing.\n\n## Repository Structure\n\n- `lkmpg.tex`: entire book, flat `\\section` numbering, uses `minted` for code\n- `lib/codeblock.tex`: `\\samplec[first][last]{path}` includes C source; never paste code inline in `.tex`; also defines `\\code`, `\\codebash`, `\\cpp{}`, and `\\sh{}`\n- `lib/kernelsrc.tex`: `\\src{path}` links to kernel source on `git.kernel.org`\n- `examples/`: kernel modules pulled into the book via `\\samplec`; standard kbuild (`obj-m`); multi-object example: `startstop-objs := start.o stop.o`\n- `examples/other/`: userspace companion programs\n- `.ci/non-working`: modules excluded from CI `insmod`/`rmmod` because they are hardware-dependent or disruptive\n\n## Adding a Module\n\nCreate `examples/foo.c`, add `obj-m += foo.o` to `example